President Trump delivered remarks in the East Room of the White House, highlighting his administration's efforts to protect the environment and promote clean air and water. He emphasized the importance of balancing economic growth with environmental conservation and touted the achievements of his administration, such as reducing emissions and improving access to clean drinking water. The President also discussed initiatives to address marine litter and debris, promote forest management, and expand outdoor recreation opportunities. He praised the work of his cabinet members and invited representatives from the fishing and outdoor recreation industries to share their experiences. Overall, the President emphasized his commitment to protecting America's natural resources and promoting a healthy environment for future generations.